FeedEntry.create(:id => 327, :name => "The Ideation Switch", :summary => "...Our inability to decide on executing one specific strategy resulted in procrastination, doing irrelevant work, or just having endless brainstorming meetings without ever taking action. I've come to believe, that in order to achieve flow in startup and get the business going, you need to <strong>keep the time your team spends on alternative directions to a minimum</strong>. <img\nclass=\"alignnone  wp-image-391\" alt=\"Screen shot 2013-01-18 at 16.21.03\" src=\"http://blog.spark59.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/the_ideation_switch_1.png\" width=\"300\" />", :url => "http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AshMaurya/~3/kejFVwbFCpg/", :published_at => Mon, 21 Jan 2013 20:29:16 UTC +00:00, :guid => "http://www.ashmaurya.com/?p=1299", :feed_title => "Ash Maurya", :feed_id => 2)
FeedEntry.create(:id => 328, :name => "Lessons Learned in 2012", :summary => "I love this time of the year. Everyone is upbeat around the holidays. The pace is slower. It gives me time to reflect. First, thank you all for your continued support. I'd like to share some of my biggest lessons learned in 2012.\n<img\nsrc=\"http://ash.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/Spark59-card.jpg\" height=\"225\" />", :url => "http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AshMaurya/~3/gk2XX13iK8M/", :published_at => Tue, 01 Jan 2013 18:11:41 UTC +00:00, :guid => "http://www.ashmaurya.com/?p=1290", :feed_title => "Ash Maurya", :feed_id => 2)
FeedEntry.create(:id => 329, :name => "Case-Study: How A Scrappy Bootstrapped Team In The Middle Of Nowhere Used Lean Startup To Achieve Startup Success", :summary => "This is a great case-study on the \"big middle\" by Garrett Moon, TodayMade.\nI often talk about how most customer learning happens at the tail-ends of the product development cycle - while you're gathering requirements and after you release your product. There is a \"big middle\" where the temptation is high for spending several weeks, months, years building and perfecting the solution. This is often where we also go astray and either build too much or build the wrong product.\n<img\nsrc=\"http://todaymade.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/homepage-todaylaunch.jpg\" width=\"300\" />", :url => "http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AshMaurya/~3/0KvKxrr2rIY/", :published_at => Tue, 27 Nov 2012 14:51:43 UTC +00:00, :guid => "http://www.ashmaurya.com/?p=1265", :feed_title => "Ash Maurya", :feed_id => 2)
FeedEntry.create(:id => 330, :name => "How We Use Lean Stack for Innovation Accounting", :summary => "I introduced Lean Stack in my last 2 posts. This is a follow-up on how we are using Lean Stack today as our Innovation Accounting framework.\n<img\nsrc=\"http://ash.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/Screen-Shot-2012-09-25-at-5.17.35-PM.png\" width=\"300\" />", :url => "http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AshMaurya/~3/lHa2099Bk8Y/", :published_at => Tue, 25 Sep 2012 22:19:24 UTC +00:00, :guid => "http://www.ashmaurya.com/?p=1252", :feed_title => "Ash Maurya", :feed_id => 2)
FeedEntry.create(:id => 331, :name => "How to Get Early Customers to Respond to Your Cold Emails", :summary => "This is a guest post from Robert Graham &#8211; a solo bootstrapper who blogs about the experience. Robert has been working in software since 2005. He is a Ph.D. dropout who spent time working for Google. Someday he &#8216;d like to work for himself. You can learn more about his approach to developing customer relationships [...]", :url => "http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AshMaurya/~3/A_anSSPOMBs/", :published_at => Thu, 30 Aug 2012 03:57:41 UTC +00:00, :guid => "http://www.ashmaurya.com/?p=1250", :feed_title => "Ash Maurya", :feed_id => 2)
FeedEntry.create(:id => 332, :name => "The Lean Stack – Part 2", :summary => "Last time, I outlined the thought process behind the Lean Stack and provided a 3000-foot overview of the toolset. In this post, I'm going to dive a little deeper into the process flow and end with a concrete case-study.\n<img\nsrc=\"http://ash.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Screen-Shot-2012-06-14-at-7.50.40-AM-608x193.png\" alt=\"\" title=\"Wired Lean Stack \" width=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-1230\" />", :url => "http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AshMaurya/~3/4B_XlPPjzAc/", :published_at => Wed, 27 Jun 2012 12:07:47 UTC +00:00, :guid => "http://www.ashmaurya.com/?p=1235", :feed_title => "Ash Maurya", :feed_id => 2)
FeedEntry.create(:id => 333, :name => "The Lean Stack – Part 1", :summary => "Even though running experiments is a key activity in Lean Startups, correctly defining, running, and tracking them is hard. After a few iterations and a lot of testing, we have developed a process that works for us and half a dozen other startups - something we're calling a lean stack.\n<img\nsrc=\"http://ash.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Screen-Shot-2012-06-13-at-9.13.29-PM.png\" width=\"200\" />", :url => "http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AshMaurya/~3/zG7gGLbwKXM/", :published_at => Thu, 14 Jun 2012 15:14:45 UTC +00:00, :guid => "http://www.ashmaurya.com/?p=1208", :feed_title => "Ash Maurya", :feed_id => 2)
FeedEntry.create(:id => 334, :name => "Why Lean Canvas vs Business Model Canvas?", :summary => "I often get asked why I created a different adaptation from the original <a\nhref=\"http://www.businessmodelgeneration.com/canvas\" target=\"_blank\">Business Model Canvas</a> by Alex Osterwalder. Lately, this question has bubbled up in frequency which is why I decided to take the time to outline the thought process that went into creating Lean Canvas. <img\nsrc=\"http://ash.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/Screen-Shot-2012-02-27-at-12.32.55-PM-608x402.png\" alt=\"\" title=\"What happens here?\" width=\"400\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-1200\" /> ", :url => "http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AshMaurya/~3/j8_q4OaCeSE/", :published_at => Mon, 27 Feb 2012 19:36:13 UTC +00:00, :guid => "http://www.ashmaurya.com/?p=1197", :feed_title => "Ash Maurya", :feed_id => 2)
FeedEntry.create(:id => 335, :name => "Spark59 Manifesto", :summary => "In his book, <a\nhref=\"http://theleanstartup.com/book\" target=\"_blank\">The Lean Startup</a>, Eric Ries describes the constant challenge entrepreneurs face between \"Pivoting and Persevering\", but he doesn't describe the even harder challenge of deciding when to hit the reset button. <img\nsrc=\"http://ash.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/Golden-Circle-608x336.png\" alt=\"\" title=\"Spark59 - Golden Circle\" width=\"400\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-374\" />", :url => "http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AshMaurya/~3/F6rhKILOPoo/", :published_at => Fri, 10 Feb 2012 21:07:15 UTC +00:00, :guid => "http://www.ashmaurya.com/?p=1194", :feed_title => "Ash Maurya", :feed_id => 2)
